NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC Attachment MM ? NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC MULTI-VALUE PROJECT CHARGE 1. Multi-Value Projects: This Attachment MM-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (?Attachment MM- NextEra?) sets forth the method for calculating and collecting the charges associated with Multi- Value Projects (?MVPs?) and for distributing the revenues associated with such charges in accordance with Schedules 26-A and 39. This Attachment MM-NextEra applies to those MVPs that are determined under Attachment FF to be subject to this Attachment MM-NextEra that are not subject to the cost recovery provisions of Attachment N. The charges under this Attachment MM-NextEra shall be in addition to any charges under Schedules 7, 8, 9, 26, 37, and 38. 2. Multi-Value Projects Annual Revenue Requirements (?MVP Revenue Requirements?): (a) Each year, in accordance with the provisions of Attachment FF, the Transmission Provider shall publish a cumulative list of all eligible MVPs by Transmission Owner and/or ITC, or that will be Competitive Transmission Projects, by Project in Appendix A of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (?MISO?) Transmission Expansion Plan (?MTEP?). (b) The revenue requirement for each MVP shall be the annual revenue requirement as computed in Section 3 below. In conjunction with providing its annual Attachment O-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (?Attachment O- NextEra?), NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (?NEET Midwest?)
2 shall furnish to the Transmission Provider its annual revenue requirement for each MVP subject to this Attachment MM-NextEra as calculated in Section 3 below. (c) For purposes of preparing the Attachment MM-NextEra, NEET Midwest must utilize the same test period that is utilized in the preparation of its Attachment O- NextEra. (d) Projects included in Attachment MM-NextEra must be in-service prior to or during the test period indicated in (c) above. If NEET Midwest receives Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (?Commission?) approval to include specific MVP projects that are recorded in construction work in progress (?CWIP?) but not yet in-service in the annual revenue requirement calculation, those projects may be included in Attachment MM-NextEra provided NEET Midwest supplies the Transmission Provider with evidence of Commission approval. (e) In order to prevent over recovery of Attachment O-NextEra revenue, the revenue requirement calculated pursuant to Attachment MM-NextEra (excluding any True-Up Adjustment) (Attachment MM-NextEra template, Page 2, Line 17, Column 14) will be subtracted by NEET Midwest from its Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement. (f) NEET Midwest, which utilizes a projected test period for its Attachment O- NextEra, shall determine its projected MVP Revenue Requirement for the following year concurrently with the preparation of its associated Attachment O- NextEra. (g) NEET Midwest shall make available to any interested party by publicly posting on OASIS its projected MVP Revenue Requirement, including all inputs in
3 sufficient detail to identify the components of its MVP Revenue Requirement, including any amounts representing a True-Up Adjustment, concurrently when it publicly posts on OASIS its projected revenue requirement for Attachment O- NextEra. (h) A Project?s True-Up Adjustment will be added to its individual projected Attachment MM-NextEra revenue requirement. (i) Revenue requirements for non-Transmission Owner or non-ITC Selected Developer Competitive Transmission Facilities that are MVPs for which the non- Transmission Owner or non-ITC Selected Developers or non-Transmission Owner or non-ITC Proposal Participants recover Competitive Transmission Facility revenue requirements in accordance with Schedule 48, as authorized by the Commission, will be included in the determination of the MVP Usage Rate (?MUR?) under this Attachment MM for charges and revenue distributions under Schedule 26-A. Updates to revenue requirements under Schedule 48 shall be submitted to the Transmission Provider in accordance with Schedule 48 or NEET Midwest?s designated formula rate protocols. 3. Calculation of the MVP Annual Revenue Requirement: (a) The MVP Annual Revenue Requirement shall be calculated as follows: i. Annual Allocation Factors shall be calculated for the following six (6) cost of service elements, expressed as a percentage, using the formulae included in this Attachment MM-NextEra which utilizes select entries from the currently effective Attachment O-NextEra: A. Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense
4 B. Other Operation and Maintenance Expense C. General, Intangible, and Common Depreciation Expense D. Taxes Other Than Income Taxes E. Income Taxes F. Return ii. Subsections (iii) through (x) describe the calculation of the Annual Allocation Factors using references to the Attachment O-NextEra template. iii. The Annual Allocation Factor for Transmission Operation and Maintenance shall be determined by dividing the difference of (the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 1, Column 5 less Attachment O-NextEra Page 3, Lines 1a, 2, and 7b, Column 5) by the amount of Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In- Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O- NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). iv. The Annual Allocation Factor for Other Operation and Maintenance shall be determined by dividing the difference of (amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 8, Column 5 less the Adjusted Transmission Operation and Maintenance amount calculated in (iii) above (reflected on Attachment MM-NextEra, Page 1, Line 3e)) by Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page
5 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In-Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). v. The Annual Allocation Factor for General, Intangible, and Common Depreciation Expense shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Lines 10 and 11, Column 5 by the amount of Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In-Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). vi. The Annual Allocation Factor for Other Taxes shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 20, Column 5 by the amount of Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In-Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). vii. The Annual Allocation Factor for Other Expense shall be equal to the sum of (iv), (v), and (vi) above. viii. The Annual Allocation Factor for Income Taxes shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 27,
6 Column 5 by the amount of Net Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment MM-NextEra, Page 1, Line 2. The Net Transmission Plant In-Service shall include any Unamortized Project-Related Regulatory Asset, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base, but shall not include any Start-Up Regulatory Asset (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). ix. The Annual Allocation Factor for Return on Rate Base shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 28, Column 5 by the amount of Net Transmission Plant In- Service included on Attachment MM-NextEra, Page 1, Line 2. The Net Transmission Plant In-Service shall include any Unamortized Project- Related Regulatory Asset, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base, but shall not include any Start-Up Regulatory Asset (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). x. The Annual Allocation Factor for Return shall be the sum of (viii) and (ix) above. xi. The MVP Annual Revenue Requirement for each individual project subject to this Attachment MM-NextEra shall be the sum of (1) Annual Allocation for Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense, (2) Annual Allocation for Other Expense, (3) Annual Return Charge, (4) Project Depreciation/Amortization Expense, (5) Incentive Return, if any (6) Competitive Bid Concession, and (7) any applicable True-Up Adjustment, where:
7 (1) Annual Allocation for Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense equals the Project Gross Plant multiplied by the Annual Allocation Factor for Transmission Operation and Maintenance calculated in (iii) above; (2) Annual Allocation for Other Expense equals the Project Gross Plant multiplied by the Annual Allocation Factor for Other Expense calculated in (vii) above; (3) Annual Return Charge equals the Project Net Plant multiplied by the Annual Allocation Factor for Return calculated in (x) above; (4) Project Depreciation/Amortization Expense equals the actual value booked, or projected to be booked for forward-looking rate periods, for the Project and included in the Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 9, Column 5; (5) Incentive Return equals the project?s Commission-approved Incentive Return in basis points multiplied by Attachment O- NextEra, Attachment 2, Line 28 divided by 100 times Project Net Plant; (6) Competitive Bid Concession, if any, for each project will be zero or a reduction to NEET Midwest?s revenue requirement under a commitment by NEET Midwest to MISO to charge less than NEET Midwest?s ceiling rate;
8 (7) True-Up Adjustment equals any applicable Attachment MM- NextEra true-up amount calculated under Attachment MM- NextEra True-Up Calculation Template; and (8) The Project Gross Plant and Project Net Plant values shall be the respective balances for the facilities comprising the Project as incorporated in the Gross Plant values from Attachment O-NextEra as identified in (iii), (iv), (v), and (vi) above and Net Plant values from Attachment MM-NextEra as identified in (viii) and (ix) above. These balances shall reflect any retirements or subsequent like kind replacements associated with the ongoing maintenance of the facilities identified in the project. xii. Each individual project shall be identified separately as a row of Line 15 on Page 2 of the Attachment MM-NextEra template, to be identified as Line 15a, 15b, etc. NEET Midwest shall add additional rows to Line 15 as needed to accommodate additional projects. Unamortized Abandoned Plant and CWIP will be identified in separate rows. 4. The MVP Usage Rate (?MUR?) The MUR is a MISO system-wide rate charged via Schedule 26-A. The revenue requirements used to derive the MUR are the aggregate of the revenue requirements of each Transmission Owner?s pro forma Attachment MM or company-specific Attachment MM, including Attachment MM-NextEra. As the MUR is a single, MISO system-wide rate, please refer to Section 5 of the pro forma Attachment MM for a complete description and application of the development of the MUR.
9 5. Unilateral Filing Rights Nothing contained in this Attachment MM-NextEra shall limit the right of NEET Midwest under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and consistent with the ISO Agreement to file with the Commission individually and unilaterally to recover the cost of an MVP in a manner other than that specified in this Attachment MM-NextEra, including, but not limited to recover rate incentives not specified herein and to recover the cost of MVPs through its pricing zone rates under Schedules 7, 8, and 9 as calculated pursuant to Attachment O-NextEra. 6. Competitive Bid Concessions For transmission development projects assigned to NEET Midwest as a result of the MISO competitive bidding process, NEET Midwest may, in its sole discretion, agree with MISO to apply a Competitive Bid Concession that will result in a lower net revenue requirement on a project-specific basis than that which would otherwise be produced by Attachment MM- NextEra. Any Competitive Bid Concession will appear as a zero or negative input to the formula, and will be determined on a project-specific basis using a workpaper that will be provided to interested parties as supporting documentation for each NEET Midwest Annual True-Up.

Attachment MM - NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC. Annual True-Up Procedure for NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC 1. Applicability This Attachment MM-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (?Attachment MM- NextEra?) Annual True-up Procedure shall be applicable to NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (?NEET Midwest?). 2. True-Up Procedure NEET Midwest shall determine its annual revenue requirement for the purposes of Section 2(b) of Attachment MM-NextEra using the same projected information that is used to calculate its Attachment O-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (?Attachment O- NextEra?) revenue requirement for the period beginning January 1 of each year (?Projected Year?). NEET Midwest shall recalculate its revenue requirement for each project entitled to treatment under Attachment MM-NextEra in conjunction with its annual recalculation of its Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement. NEET Midwest shall make available to any interested party its projected revenue requirement for Attachment MM-NextEra, including all inputs in sufficient detail to identify the components of NEET Midwest?s revenue requirement for Attachment MM-NextEra including any amounts representing a true-up adjustment determined as set forth below. Any adjustments to the revenue requirement relating to the difference between the actual revenue requirement and the actual revenue received for Attachment MM-NextEra (?True-Up Adjustment?) shall be determined in the following manner: (1) In the year following the Projected Year (?the Succeeding Year?), in conjunction with the next succeeding update of its Attachment O revenue requirement with actual data, completed pursuant to the Attachment O-NextEra, the actual revenue requirement for
2 Attachment MM-NextEra (calculated in accordance with Attachment MM-NextEra of the Tariff) for each project for the Projected Year shall be determined based upon the actual amounts incurred. For the Projected Year, the actual revenue requirement for each project shall be compared to the Schedule 26-A revenues distributed to NEET Midwest allocated proportionately to all projects used to determine the aggregate projected revenue requirement during the Projected Year to determine any difference between the actual revenue requirement for each project under Attachment MM-NextEra and the revenues distributed. If the actual revenue requirement for a project for the Projected Year is more than the actual revenue received during the Projected Year (i.e., an under-collection), then the difference shall be added to the revenue requirement for such project for the second year following the Projected Year (the ?True-Up Year?). If the actual revenue requirement for the Projected Year for a project is less than the actual revenue received during the Projected Year (i.e., an over-collection), then the difference shall be subtracted from the revenue requirement for that project for the True-Up Year. The differences between the actual revenue requirement and the revenue received shall be posted, on a project specific basis, to NEET Midwest?s page of the Transmission Provider?s OASIS website no later than June 1 of the Succeeding Year. Such True-Up Adjustment shall be added to or subtracted from the revenue requirement to determine the revenue requirement for the True-Up Year as determined in accordance with Attachment MM-NextEra. Interest on the aggregate difference between the actual revenue requirement and the aggregate revenue received will be determined as set forth below and shall be allocated proportionately to each project?s contribution to the aggregate difference and then added to or subtracted from their respective revenue
3 requirement for the True-Up Year to determine the total revenue requirement for the True-Up Year. NEET Midwest shall provide explanations of true-up amounts and the corresponding interest calculations in response to inquiries and shall post on the Transmission Provider?s OASIS website information regarding frequently asked questions. (2) Interest on any aggregate over recovery of the revenue requirement shall be determined based on the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission?s (?Commission?) regulation at 18 C.F.R ? 35.19a. Interest on any aggregate under recovery of the revenue requirement shall be determined using the interest rate equal to: (i) NEET Midwest?s actual short-term debt costs, capped at the interest rate determined based on the Commission?s regulation at 18 C.F.R. ? 35.19a; or (ii) if NEET Midwest does not have short-term debt, then the interest rate determined based on the Commission?s regulation at 18 C.F.R ? 35.19a. An average interest rate will be used to calculate the time value of money for the twenty-four (24) months during which the over or under recovery in the revenue requirement exists. The average interest rate will be determined using the same period as is used for NEET Midwest?s Attachment O-NextEra true-up calculation. The resulting interest component of the true-up will be included in the Attachment MM-NextEra revenue requirement for the True-Up Year. (3) The revenue requirement for Attachment MM-NextEra for the True-Up Year shall be the sum of the Attachment MM-NextEra revenue requirement for the True-Up Year, plus or minus the true-up from the Projected Year, if any, including the average interest for two years, as explained above.
4 3. Example Assumptions: NEET Midwest?s projected 2017 revenue requirement for an Attachment MM project is $2,000,000. NEET Midwest?s actual 2017 revenue requirement for the Attachment MM project calculated based on financial data available in May 2018 is $1,950,000. Actual 2017 Schedule 26-A revenues distributed to NEET Midwest for the project are $1,976,250. True-Up Calculation (Assumes one Project used to determine Projected Revenue Requirement): There is an over recovery of the revenue requirement equal to $26,250 ($1,976,250 - $1,950,000 = $26,250). The True-Up Adjustment with interest shall be included in the 2019 revenue requirement for Attachment MM-NextEra and estimated rates that shall be made available to any interested party in conjunction with NEET Midwest?s posting of its 2019 projected Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement. The new rates will take effect on January 1, 2019.

Attachment GG NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC
NETWORK UPGRADE CHARGE 1. Network Upgrade Cost Allocation: This Attachment GG-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (Attachment GG- NextEra) sets forth the method for calculating and collecting the charges associated with Network Upgrades and for distributing the revenues associated with such charges. This Attachment applies to those Network Upgrades that are determined under Attachment FF to be subject to this Attachment GG-NextEra that are not subject to the cost recovery provisions of Attachment N. The charges under this Attachment GG-NextEra shall be in addition to any charges under Schedules 7, 8, 9, 26-A, and 39. 2. Determination of Network Upgrade Charge (NUC): (a) The Transmission Provider shall identify in this Attachment GG-NextEra all Network Upgrades eligible under Attachment FF that form the basis of the NUC. Such designations shall be the same as those made for the relevant Network Upgrades in the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) Transmission Expansion Plan (MTEP). The NUC for each eligible project shall be its adjusted annual revenue requirement as computed in Section 3 below. In conjunction with providing its annual Attachment O-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (Attachment O-NextEra), NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (NEET Midwest) shall furnish to the Transmission Provider: (1) its NUC for each Network Upgrade subject to this Attachment GG-
NextEra as calculated below; and (2) its twelve (12) monthly transmission system peaks determined in accordance with Attachment O-NextEra. (b) The Transmission Provider shall apportion the NUC from (a) above in accordance with the applicable Attachment FF. (c) For purposes of preparing Attachment GG-NextEra, NEET Midwest must utilize the same test period that is utilized in the preparation of its Attachment O- NextEra. (d) Projects included in Attachment GG-NextEra must be in-service prior to or during the test period indicated in (c) above. If NEET Midwest receives Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) approval to include specific Network Upgrades that are recorded in construction work in progress (CWIP) but not yet in-service in the annual revenue requirement calculation, and the Transmission Provider includes such Network Upgrades on Appendix A of the MTEP, those projects may be included in Attachment GG-NextEra provided NEET Midwest supplies the Transmission Provider with evidence of FERC approval. (e) In order to prevent over recovery of Attachment O-NextEra revenue, the revenue requirement calculated pursuant to Attachment GG-NextEra (Attachment GG- NextEra template, Page 2, Line 17, Column 14) will be subtracted by NEET Midwest from its Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement. (f) The NUC is a zonal rate charged via Schedule 26. The Network Upgrade annual revenue requirement apportioned to a pricing zone shall be the sum of all Transmission Owner and/or ITC NUCs for the pricing zone including those NUCs allocated on a system-wide basis to all pricing zones as provided under 2 Attachment FF, or to pricing zones in a specific Planning Area where a project terminates exclusively pursuant to Attachment FF-6. Section 2 of the Transmission Providers pro forma Attachment GG provides a complete description of the development and application of the NUC. (g) Revenue requirements for non-Transmission Owner or non-ITC Selected Developer Competitive Transmission Facilities that are not Multi-Value Projects for which the non-Transmission Owner or non-ITC Selected Developers or non- Transmission Owner or non-ITC Proposal Participants recover Competitive Transmission Facility revenue requirements in accordance with Schedule 48, as authorized by FERC, will be included in the determination of the NUC under this Attachment GG for charges and revenue distributions under Schedule 26. Updates to revenue requirements under Schedule 48 shall be submitted to the Transmission Provider in accordance with Schedule 48 or NEET Midwests designated formula rate protocols. 3. Calculation of the NUC: (a) The NUC shall be allocated as follows: (1) Annual Allocation Factors shall be calculated for the following six (6) cost of service elements, expressed as a percentage, using the formulae included in this Attachment GG-NextEra which utilizes select entries from the currently effective Attachment O-NextEra: a. Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense b. Other Operation and Maintenance Expense c. General, Intangible, and Common Depreciation Expense 3 d. Taxes Other Than Income Taxes e. Income Taxes f. Return (2) Subsections (3) through (10) describe the calculation of the Annual Allocation Factors using references to the Attachment O-NextEra template. (3) The Annual Allocation Factor for Transmission Operation and Maintenance shall be determined by dividing the difference of (the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 1, Column 5 less Attachment O-NextEra Page 3, Lines 1a, 2, and 7b, Column 5) by the amount of Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In- Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O- NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). (4) The Annual Allocation Factor for Other Operation and Maintenance shall be determined by dividing the difference of (amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 8, Column 5 less the Adjusted Transmission Operation and Maintenance amount calculated in (3) above (reflected on Attachment GG-NextEra, Page 1, Line 3e)) by Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In-Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, 4 or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). (5) The Annual Allocation Factor for General, Intangible, and Common Depreciation Expense shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Lines 10 and 11, Column 5 by the amount of Gross Transmission Plant In-Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In-Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). (6) The Annual Allocation Factor for Taxes Other Than Income Taxes shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 20, Column 5 by the amount of Gross Transmission Plant In- Service included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Line 2, Column 5. The Gross Transmission Plant In-Service shall not include Unamortized Regulatory Assets, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). (7) The Annual Allocation Factor for Other Expense shall be equal to the sum of (4), (5), and (6) above. (8) The Annual Allocation Factor for Income Taxes shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 27, Column 5 by the amount of Net Transmission Plant In-Service included 5 on Attachment GG-NextEra, Page 1, Line 2. The Net Transmission Plant In-Service shall include any Unamortized Project-Related Regulatory Asset, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base, but shall not include any Start-Up Regulatory Asset (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). (9) The Annual Allocation Factor for Return on Rate Base shall be determined by dividing the amount included on Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 28, Column 5 by the amount of Net Transmission Plant In- Service included on Attachment GG-NextEra, Page 1, Line 2. The Net Transmission Plant In-Service shall include any Unamortized Project- Related Regulatory Asset, Unamortized Abandoned Plant, or CWIP included in Rate Base, but shall not include any Start-Up Regulatory Asset (Attachment O-NextEra, Page 2, Lines 18a, 23a, and 23b, Column 5). (10) The Annual Allocation Factor for Return shall be the sum of (8) and (9) above. (11) The NUC to be used in Schedule 26 for each individual Project subject to this Attachment GG-NextEra shall be the sum of the Projects (a) Annual Allocation for Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense, (b) Annual Allocation for Other Expense, (c) Annual Return Charge, (d) Project Depreciation/Amortization Expense, (e) Incentive Return, (f) Competitive Bid Concession, and (g) any applicable True-Up Adjustment, where: 6 (a) Annual Allocation for Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense equals the Project Gross Plant multiplied by the Annual Allocation Factor for Transmission Operation and Maintenance Expense calculated in (3) above; (b) Annual Allocation for Other Expense equals the Project Gross Plant multiplied by the Annual Allocation Factor for Other Expense calculated in (7) above; (c) Annual Return Charge equals the Project Net Plant multiplied by the Annual Allocation Factor for Return calculated in (10) above; (d) Project Depreciation/Amortization Expense equals the actual value booked, or projected to be booked for forward-looking rate periods, for the Project and included in the Attachment O-NextEra, Page 3, Line 9, Column 5; (g) True-Up Adjustment equals any applicable Attachment GG- NextEra true-up amount calculated under Attachment GG-NextEra True-Up Calculation Template; and 7 (h) The Project Gross Plant and Project Net Plant values shall be the respective balances for the facilities comprising the project as incorporated in the Gross Plant values from Attachment O-NextEra as identified in (3), (4), (5), and (6) above and the Net Plant values from Attachment GG-NextEra as identified in (8) and (9) above. Attachment GG - NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC
Annual True-Up Procedure for NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC
1. Applicability This Attachment GG-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (Attachment GG- NextEra) Annual True-Up Procedure shall apply to all transmission projects of NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (NEET Midwest) where the individual project or construction work in progress (CWIP) annual revenue requirement is calculated pursuant to Attachment GG-NextEra for cost recovery under Schedule 26 of this Tariff. 2. True-Up Procedure NEET Midwest shall determine its annual revenue requirement for the purposes of Section 2(a) of Attachment GG-NextEra using the same projected information that is used to calculate its Attachment O-NextEra Energy Transmission Midwest, LLC (Attachment O- NextEra) revenue requirement for the period beginning January 1 of each year (Projected Year). NEET Midwest shall recalculate its revenue requirement for each project entitled to treatment under Attachment GG-NextEra in conjunction with its annual recalculation of its Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement. NEET Midwest shall make available to any interested party its projected revenue requirement for Attachment GG-NextEra, including all inputs in sufficient detail to identify the components of NEET Midwests revenue requirement for Attachment GG-NextEra including any amounts representing a true-up adjustment determined as set forth below. Any adjustments to the revenue requirement relating to the difference between the actual revenue requirement and the actual revenue received for Attachment GG-NextEra (True-Up Adjustment) shall be determined in the following manner:
(1) In the year following the Projected Year (the Succeeding Year), in conjunction with the next succeeding update of its Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement with actual data, completed pursuant to the Attachment O-NextEra, the actual revenue requirement for Attachment GG-NextEra (calculated in accordance with Attachment GG-NextEra of the Tariff) for each project for the Projected Year shall be determined based upon the actual amounts incurred. For the Projected Year, the actual revenue requirement for each project shall be compared to the Schedule 26 revenues distributed to NEET Midwest allocated proportionately to all projects used to determine the aggregate projected revenue requirement during the Projected Year to determine any difference between the actual revenue requirement for each project under Attachment GG-NextEra and the revenues distributed. If the actual revenue requirement for a project for the Projected Year is more than the actual revenue received during the Projected Year (i.e., an under- collection), then the difference shall be added to the revenue requirement for such project for the second year following the Projected Year (the True-Up Year). If the actual revenue requirement for the Projected Year for a project is less than the actual revenue received during the Projected Year (i.e., an over-collection), then the difference shall be subtracted from the revenue requirement for that project for the True-Up Year. The differences between the actual revenue requirement and the revenue received shall be posted, on a project specific basis, to NEET Midwests page of the Transmission Providers OASIS website no later than June 1 of the Succeeding Year. Such True-Up Adjustment shall be added to or subtracted from the revenue requirement to determine the revenue requirement for the True-Up Year as determined in accordance with Attachment GG-NextEra. Interest on the aggregate difference between the actual revenue 2 requirement and the aggregate revenue received will be determined as set forth below and shall be allocated proportionately to each projects contribution to the aggregate difference and then added to or subtracted from their respective revenue requirement for the True-Up Year to determine the total revenue requirement for the True-Up Year. NEET Midwest shall provide explanations of true-up amounts and the corresponding interest calculations in response to inquiries and shall post on the Transmission Providers OASIS website information regarding frequently asked questions. (2) Interest on any aggregate over recovery of the revenue requirement shall be determined based on the Federal Energy Regulatory Commissions (Commission) regulation at 18 C.F.R § 35.19a. Interest on any aggregate under recovery of the revenue requirement shall be determined using the interest rate equal to: (i) NEET Midwests actual short-term debt costs, capped at the interest rate determined based on the Commissions regulation at 18 C.F.R § 35.19a; or (ii) if NEET Midwest does not have short-term debt, then the interest rate determined based on the Commissions regulation at 18 C.F.R § 35.19a. An average interest rate will be used to calculate the time value of money for the twenty-four (24) months during which the over or under recovery in the revenue requirement exists. The average interest rate will be determined using the same period as is used for NEET Midwests Attachment O-NextEra true-up calculation. The resulting interest component of the true-up will be included in the Attachment GG-NextEra revenue requirement for the True-Up Year. (3) The revenue requirement for Attachment GG-NextEra for the True-Up Year shall be the sum of the Attachment GG-NextEra revenue requirement for the True-Up Year, plus or 3 minus the true-up from the Projected Year, if any, including the average interest for two years, as explained above. 3. Example Assumptions: NEET Midwests projected 2017 revenue requirement for an Attachment GG project is $4,000,000. NEET Midwests actual 2017 revenue requirement for the Attachment GG project calculated based on financial data available in May 2018 is $3,950,000. Actual 2017 Schedule 26 revenues distributed to NEET Midwest for the project are $3,976,250. True-Up Calculation (Assumes one Project used to determine Projected Revenue Requirement): There is an over recovery of the revenue requirement equal to $26,250 ($3,976,250 - $3,950,000 = $26,250). The True-Up Adjustment with interest shall be included in the 2019 revenue requirement for Attachment GG-NextEra and estimated rates that shall be made available to any interested party in conjunction with NEET Midwests posting of its 2019 projected Attachment O-NextEra revenue requirement.
